2941
04:56:48,000 --> 04:56:53,000
What effect might wake boats have on other lake users?

2942
04:56:53,000 --> 04:56:59,500
The most obvious is the generation of large waves, which they do well.

2943
04:56:59,500 --> 04:57:05,500
It's something that these boats were created for in the first place.

2944
04:57:05,500 --> 04:57:12,000
These large waves, however, are created where there are no such natural waves.

2945
04:57:12,000 --> 04:57:21,500
The unexpected waves can surprise or even capsize boaters, especially those in small boats such as kayaks and canoes.

2946
04:57:21,500 --> 04:57:32,000
And as I said, it can even surprise people on floating docks when they find their dock is no longer stable.

2947
04:57:32,000 --> 04:57:44,500
The waves resulting from wake boats passing through an area are unusual because they have a shorter wavelength, which means they may come closer together.

2948
04:57:44,500 --> 04:57:52,000
They are steeper, which means they hit the shore, docks, swimmers, and other things harder.

2949
04:57:52,000 --> 04:57:56,500
They come from different directions from normal wind-created waves.

2950
04:57:56,500 --> 04:58:07,500
As a result, people can be surprised because the waves are not the way a normal wind-driven wave would be to them.

2951
04:58:07,500 --> 04:58:27,000
And I've tried to get into kayaks and canoes sometimes when I misjudged when a wave was going to come to us, and it would come close to capsizing at my dock, which is something I'd rather not do.

2952
04:58:27,000 --> 04:58:34,500
The thing about wake boats is that they cannot legislate away from having big waves.

2953
04:58:34,500 --> 04:58:38,000
That's the whole purpose behind those boats.

2954
04:58:38,000 --> 04:58:52,500
Although I have learned just in the last few days that they can have some influence about where those waves are directed, and I'm delighted to see that happen.

2955
04:58:52,500 --> 04:59:22,000
The last thing that concerns me is that the wake boats will stir up the water and thus the sediment and have the possibility of freeing up nutrients that is currently within the sediments and giving more food for cyanobacteria blooms, which is something I'm sure most everyone in this room knows and would like to avoid very assiduously.

2956
04:59:22,000 --> 04:59:28,500
And so I'm just cautious about anything that would give cyanobacteria a foothold.

2957
04:59:28,500 --> 04:59:34,000
So I would request that you vote for the HB 1071.

2958
04:59:34,000 --> 04:59:42,000
I think it would give all boat users a chance at using the state's lake assets.

2959
04:59:42,000 --> 05:00:07,500
but because in many places canoes and kayaks are simply not feasible to be used when you're in close proximity to a wakeboat, I think that we have to allow some places where wakeboats are not allowed so that the canoes and kayaks have some safe places to play as well.

