3028
05:07:05,500 --> 05:07:07,500
What's 100 feet?

3029
05:07:07,500 --> 05:07:11,500
Well, in a lake like mine, it's detrimental.

3030
05:07:11,500 --> 05:07:13,500
It's punitive.

3031
05:07:13,500 --> 05:07:18,500
It pretty much will suffocate the ability to do so.

3032
05:07:18,500 --> 05:07:33,000
And frankly, I think it's premature for a bill at this time to be passed based on a University of Minnesota study, which frankly is inconclusive in my mind.

3033
05:07:33,000 --> 05:07:42,500
If you read the details, it's four boats, two surf boats, a recreational boat, and a competition ski boat.

3034
05:07:42,500 --> 05:08:00,000
A competition ski boat is designed specifically to skim across the top of the water and make no wave behind it whatsoever so that skiers at high speed can ski without any sort of obstruction.

3035
05:08:00,000 --> 05:08:17,500
When you amortize the data in a way that they did, it fits a certain narrative, and certain narrative is the reason that this bill is put in 40 today with an arbitrary 250 feet.

3036
05:08:17,500 --> 05:08:25,000
This at its core is an education issue, not a legislation issue in my opinion.

3037
05:08:25,000 --> 05:09:19,500
On our lake, we consistently preach situational awareness courtesy being alert as a driver understanding the cause of your actions when voting being short just being a good neighbor and I think that we as New Hampshire residents are more than capable of handling this issue with better education and if the state wants to get involved my suggestion is why don't we have a little more attention thrown towards the New Hampshire boater licensing process in that educational scenario in which we gloss over the good boating practices and focus way too much on ocean-going vessels for which a very small percentage of New Hampshire boats are registered.

3038
05:09:19,500 --> 05:09:24,500
The majority of New Hampshire boats are registered on lakes.

3039
05:09:24,500 --> 05:09:28,500
So why isn't there more focus on lakes?

3040
05:09:28,500 --> 05:10:09,000
Now that this sport has exploded and created a tremendous amount of demand to get into the sport, which frankly has also created real estate demand on lakefronts, which drove up property prices, which drove up tax income, revenue, and things along those lines, it's an important issue, and I know it's got the ear of some people, or the ire, I should say, of some people that kind of view it as an easy thing to point at as problems.

3041
05:10:09,000 --> 05:10:16,000
But in my opinion, if we segregate this sport at this point, it's premature.

3042
05:10:16,000 --> 05:10:29,500
There's not enough data to support it, and I think the community as a whole has rallied behind wanting to make it a safer and better place.

3043
05:10:29,500 --> 05:10:33,000
The 150-foot setback is just a guide.

3044
05:10:33,000 --> 05:10:45,500
Most folks, as has been testified here today, they seek the largest area of water possible and try to do so in a respectful way.

3045
05:10:45,500 --> 05:10:49,500
These boats aren't typically operated by young kids.

3046
05:10:49,500 --> 05:10:52,000
It's typically fathers like myself.

3047
05:10:52,000 --> 05:10:59,000
